        The reactant is a monomer, ethene. Ethene will be liquid at room temperature. Ethene's longest chain of carbons is 2, and the carbons are bonded by double bonds, so ethene is unsaturated. In contrast, polyethene can have carbon chains of infinite length, is solid at room temperature, and all bonds in polyethene are single bonds so it is saturated.
