    a.
        i.
            2PbS + 2O2 -> 2PbO + S2O2
        ii.
            Sulfur dioxide should not be released into the atmosphere as it can cause acid rain, which is bad for the environment.
        iii.
            moles of lead oxide = 892 * 10^6 / 233 = 4000000 moles.
            There are half as many moles of CO2, so 2000000. So, 2000000 * 44 = 88000000 = 88 tonnes.
        iv?
            Lead (II) sulfide is a solid with a very high melting point at room temperature because the ions in lead sulfide have strong electrostatic forces of attraction with each other in a lattice structure, which requires a lot of energy to overcome, so have a high melting point. The ions are held fixed in place by those strong electrostatic forces of attraction. 

            Sulfur dioxide has weak intermolecular forces of attraction between molecules of sulfur dioxide. When heated, these weak forces are overcome, allowing the sulfur dioxide molecules to move past each other freely, and hence be gaseous.
